    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The test samples factor addresses variability arising from physical specimen-to-specimen manufacturing variation in validation experiments. For this COU, validation is performed against the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark geometry, which is a single canonical reference geometry with no production-level manufacturing variability. All experimental measurements use the same pump specimen under controlled laboratory conditions. Specimen-to-specimen variability is therefore not a factor in this validation activity, and this factor is not applicable at MRL 2 for a benchmark-geometry study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The equivalency of input parameters factor applies when validation experiments are conducted on a surrogate or scaled model that differs from the clinical or production device, requiring demonstration that the input parameter space of the surrogate maps equivalently to the target device. In this COU, the CFD model is validated directly against the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark under CPB-representative conditions using the same geometry and operating parameters as the COU. No surrogate scaling or parameter mapping is required. Consequently, this factor is not applicable to the present validation approach."
